data.title: Paul Jordaan
data.text:
Paul Abraham Jordaan (born (1992-01-04)4 January 1992) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is either fly-half or centre. He represents La Rochelle in the French Top 14.

He was a member of the South Africa Under 20 team that competed in the 2011 IRB Junior World Championship [1] and won the 2012 tournament.[2]
